thumb|220x220px|Lunkwill and Fook, as seen in the fourth episode of the BBC television series (1980).
Lunkwill was one of the two programmers chosen to make the great question to Deep Thought on the day of the Great On-Turning, the other being Fook. He was the ancestor of Loonquawl, whose name was essentially identical, merely spelt differently. Radio 

